English premier division club Aston  Villa defeated local side Manning Rangers 1-0 here Tuesday night in an  international festival match watched by a crowd of 8,000.
Courageous defending by Rangers, a mid-table South African first division  club, kept Villa in check until the 48th minute when striker Guy Whittingham  beat goalkeeper Neil Blankenberg.
The festival continues Thursday when Cape Town Spurs host another English  team, Liverpool.
